        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 8 at 5:42PM EDT by NWS Blacksburg VA</headline>
        <description>At 542 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Cornwall, or near Buena Vista, moving east at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Lexington...
Rockbridge Baths...
Cornwall...
Alto...
Fairfield...
Brownsburg...
and Vesuvius.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 900 PM EDT for
central and south central Virginia.</instruction>
